04224nam a22006975i 9781442670556DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20172004onc    fo  d z      eng d  a97814426705567 a10.3138/97814426705562doi  a(DE-B1597)483199  a(OCoLC)1004882433  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aonccCA-ON 4aGN667.W5P65 2005 7aSOC0020102bisacsh04a305.89/915094151 aPoirier, Sylvie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut12aA World of Relationships :bItineraries, Dreams, and Events in the Australian Western Desert /cSylvie Poirier. 1aToronto : bUniversity of Toronto Press, c[2017] 4c©2004  a1 online resource (220 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aAnthropological Horizons00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 1. A Place like Balgo: A Story of Accommodation, Resistance, and Misunderstandings -- tChapter 2. Ancestrality, Sentient Places, and Social Spaces -- tChapter 3. Sociality, Mobility, and Composite Identity -- tChapter 4. Ways of Being, Relating, and Knowing -- tChapter 5. The Social Setting of Dreams and Dreaming -- tChapter 6. Ritual Vitality and Mobility -- tConclusion: Ancestrality, Imaginary, and Historicity -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA World of Relationships is an ethnographical account and anthropological study of the cultural use and social potential of dreams among Aboriginal groups of the Australian Western Desert. The outcome of fieldwork conducted in the area in the 1980s and 90s, it was originally published in French as Les jardins du nomade: Cosmologie, territoire et personne dans le désert occidental australien.In her study, Sylvie Poirier explores the contemporary Aboriginal system of knowledge and law through an analysis of the relationships between the ancestral order, the 'sentient' land, and human agencies. At the ethnographical and analytical levels, particular attention is given to a range of local narratives and stories, and to the cultural construction of individual experiences. Poirier also investigates the cultural system of dreams and dreaming, and the process of their socialization, analysing their ideological, semantic, pragmatic, and experiential dimensions. Through the synthesis of a complex and diverse range of theoretical and empirical materials, A World of Relationships offers new insights into Australian Aboriginal sociality, historicity, and dynamics of cultural change and ritual innovation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAboriginal AustralianszAustraliazWestern Desert (W.A.)xSocial life and customs. 0aDreamtime (Aboriginal Australian mythology)zAustraliazWestern Desert (W.A.). 0aMythology, Aboriginal AustralianzAustraliazWestern Desert (W.A.). 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267055640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442670556423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442670556.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK